description:
DistributedModule.tsx uses if/else chains for canvas (~:4805), controls (~:4281), and properties (~:2980). Adding a new sim to DistributedSim union doesn't force adding cases — TypeScript won't warn. Silent blank canvas results.

Replace with exhaustive switch + never assertion:
```typescript
function getCanvas(sim: DistributedSim): React.ReactNode {
  switch (sim) {
    case 'raft': return <RaftCanvas ... />;
    case 'consistent-hashing': return <ConsistentHashCanvas ... />;
    // ... all 11 cases
    default: {
      const _exhaustive: never = sim;
      throw new Error(`Unknown simulation: ${_exhaustive}`);
    }
  }
}
```

Now adding 'consistent-broadcast' to the union creates a TypeScript error at every switch. This is the SINGLE biggest DX improvement for type safety.

Common developer mistakes produce silent failures:
1. Add sim to DistributedSim but forget SIMULATIONS array → sim ID exists but has no name/description, won't appear in sidebar
2. Add sim to SIMULATIONS but forget canvas switch case → appears in sidebar, clicking shows blank canvas, no error
3. Forget module-progress entry → sim works but progress not tracked

Add runtime checks:
```typescript
// In useDistributedModule, on mount:
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
  for (const sim of ['raft', 'consistent-hashing', ...] as DistributedSim[]) {
    if (!SIMULATIONS.find(s => s.id === sim)) {
      console.error(`[Distributed] Simulation '${sim}' is in DistributedSim type but missing from SIMULATIONS array`);
    }
  }
}
```

Similar checks for canvas/controls/properties completeness.

The orphaned visualizers (RaftVisualizer.tsx, ConsistentHashRingVisualizer.tsx, VectorClockDiagram.tsx) are a developer TRAP. A contributor looking for 'where is the Raft visualization' would find RaftVisualizer.tsx first, modify it, and wonder why nothing changes. The active visualizations are inside DistributedModule.tsx.

Until DIS-024 (god file split) + DIS-025 (integrate orphaned vizzes) are done, add a prominent warning comment at the top of each orphaned file:
```
// ⚠️ WARNING: This component is NOT currently used by the distributed module.
// The active Raft visualization is embedded in DistributedModule.tsx:175-407.
// See DIS-024 and DIS-025 for the plan to integrate this component.
// DO NOT MODIFY THIS FILE expecting changes to appear in the app.
```
